import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { AiOutlineMenu, AiOutlineClose } from 'react-icons/ai';

import { NavLink, Logo, List, NavList, Wrapper, Nav, Bars, Close  } from './FakeNavElements';


const FakeNavBar = () => {
  const [isMobile, setIsMobile] = useState(false);

  return (
    <Wrapper>
      <Nav className= "navbar">
        <Logo className="fake-logo">Logo</Logo>
        <NavList className="nav-links">
          <NavLink to="/">
            <List>
              Home
            </List>
          </NavLink>
          <NavLink to="/petposts">
            <List>
              Posts
            </List>
          </NavLink>
          <NavLink to="/about">
            <List>
              About
            </List>
          </NavLink>
        </NavList>
        <button className="mobile-menu-icon">
          {isMobile ? <Close><AiOutlineClose /></Close> : <Bars><AiOutlineMenu /></Bars>}
        </button>
      </Nav>
    </Wrapper>
  )

}

export default FakeNavBar;
